<subSubSection id="C3576525FF1DCAE7FFFBFE56FEE6FCCA" pageId="253" pageNumber="390" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BF236AEFF1DCAE7FFFBFE56FF45FD89" blockId="253.[112,648,502,845]" box="[113,213,502,528]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236AEFF1DCAE7FFFBFDB5FF4DFC8A" blockId="253.[112,648,502,845]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">
The specimen Ferguson designated as 
<typeStatus id="54F6880CFF1DCAE7FD82FDB5FDFAFDA8" box="[520,618,533,559]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FFFBFD95FF34FDC8" box="[113,164,565,591]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">flava</emphasis>
was the specimen described and illustrated by Hoffmann (1936: 63) as the 
<typeStatus id="54F6880CFF1DCAE7FE57FDF5FDADFDE8" box="[477,573,597,623]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">holotype</typeStatus>
of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D2DFF1DCAE7FFF9FDD4FE8EFD09" box="[115,286,628,654]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390" rank="variety" variety="confluens">
variety 
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FF4BFDD4FE8EFD09" box="[193,286,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">confluens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FECEFDD4FEE6FD09" box="[324,374,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">flava</emphasis>
. The name 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D2DFF1DCAE7FE70FDD4FDC7FD09" authorityName="Kohler" authorityYear="1924" box="[506,599,628,654]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Esthema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="253" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confluens">
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FE70FDD4FDC7FD09" box="[506,599,628,654]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">confluens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was infrasubspecific and not available. Because the type specimen and type locality of 
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FE35FD14FE62FD49" box="[447,498,692,718]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">flava</emphasis>
is unknown, Ferguson chose the 
<typeStatus id="54F6880CFF1DCAE7FEDEFD73FE25FD6A" box="[340,437,723,749]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D2DFF1DCAE7FE56FD73FDACFD6A" authorityName="Kohler" authorityYear="1924" box="[476,572,723,749]" class="Insecta" family="Lepidoptera (awaiting allocation)" genus="Esthema" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="253" pageNumber="390" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confluens">
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FE56FD73FDACFD6A" box="[476,572,723,749]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">confluens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the 
<typeStatus id="54F6880CFF1DCAE7FFF9FD53FF48FC8A" box="[115,216,755,781]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF236AEFF1DCAE7FF02FCB3FEE6FCCA" blockId="253.[112,648,502,845]" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">
Hoffmann (1936: 63) described an other infrasubspecific name for 
<emphasis id="B939EABCFF1DCAE7FEB7FC93FEFFFCCA" box="[317,367,819,845]" italics="true" pageId="253" pageNumber="390">flava</emphasis>
:
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
